# Revising the form of the timestamp column in the dataset by string operations. 

date_format = "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S" 

def formatter(item): 
    item_formatted = item.replace("T"," ").replace("Z"," ").rstrip() 
    item_formatted = datetime.strptime(item_formatted, date_format)
    return item_formatted

dataset["timestamp"] = dataset["timestamp"].apply(formatter)

In [18]:
# Created a function that iterates on each row and in each row checks whether the value of the stock is out of 3 sigma limits. 

def outlier_detector(instance): 
    y_m = instance["Year-Month"]
    for stock in stocks: 
        if instance[stock] < grouped_ty_mean.loc[y_m][stock] - 3*(grouped_ty_std.loc[y_m][stock]): 
            outliers["Timestamp"].append(instance["timestamp"]) 
            outliers["Stock"].append(stock)
            outliers["Value"].append(instance[stock]) 
            outliers["Year-Month"].append(instance["Year-Month"]) 
            
        elif instance[stock] > grouped_ty_mean.loc[y_m][stock] + 3*(grouped_ty_std.loc[y_m][stock]): 
            outliers["Timestamp"].append(instance["timestamp"]) 
            outliers["Stock"].append(stock)
            outliers["Value"].append(instance[stock]) 
            outliers["Year-Month"].append(instance["Year-Month"]) 
            
        else: 
            pass
In [19]:

for i in range(0,len(two_years_interval)): 
    outlier_detector(two_years_interval.iloc[i])
